args: I accepted the job of delivering this letter\nto Remuel, but maybe I should've thought\nthings through a little more first...?
Sneaking into a manor I haven't been\ninvited to isn't the best look for a member\nof a diplomatic mission...
If I get caught, it'll be really, REALLY bad.\nBut still...
In a fair world, those star-crossed lovers\nwould be connected...so I can't let this\nsad ending stand!
I have to get this message through...\nI have to see Julia's letter delivered!
(I'll need to think of this as a battlefield—\nand if the front lines are full of enemies,\nI'll need to move quickly and carefully.)
(First, I need to observe the situation.\nI can take cover there and...)
(You've got this, Noelle... Keep calm,\nkeep cool, and keep moving!)
Er, I have a message. From Julia.\nCan you, um...open the door?
From Julia?! Can it be true?!
This is sealed with her family crest!
Oh, my sweet Julia! My heart sings to see\nyour feelings writ large across the page!
I shall pen my response immediately.\nPray tarry a moment, good messenger.
(Yay! It looks like the letter is doing\nits job to connect the two of them.)
Er, thank you, Julia. Hanging that rope\nout of your window made it a lot easier\nfor me to get into your room.
Here, this is... This is Remuel's reply.\nTo your letter, I mean.
You're sent by the Goddess herself,\nNoelle. Thank you.

If we stay in these awful houses, we'll
never be together—so if loving him
means leaving everything behind,
that's what I'm ready to do!
I told him exactly how I felt in the letter,\nand he feels exactly the same!
Oh, I don't know how I'll ever repay you.
Goodness, things are about to get busy;\nI need to discuss the details of our plan\nwith Remuel.
Your help is going to be more vital than\never in the coming days, Noelle!
(They certainly managed to connect,\nbut...now they're eloping?)
(Does that count as a happy ending?)
